Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of LDPC codes in the McEliece cryptosystem, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a procedure for selecting the density of the private parity-check matrix in the McEliece cryptosystem, which is a cryptographic system. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the decryption complexity of the McEliece cryptosystem and proposes a procedure for selecting the density of the parity-check matrix based on this complexity. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper may have implications for the societal impact of cryptography, as it proposes a way to optimize the security and efficiency of a cryptographic system. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may be of interest to software engineers who are developing or implementing the McEliece cryptosystem using LDPC codes.
